      <index>
         <point>
            <time>60</time>
            <title>Born in Vollmer, ID; name change in Troy; disliked for his lending practices</title>
            <synopsis>Born in Vollmer, Idaho. Name change to Troy. Vollmer
               disliked for his lending practices. "Biggest little
               town on earth."
               
            </synopsis>
         </point>
         <point>
            <time>300</time>
            <title>Father homesteaded in 1884; came to America from Sweden</title>
            <synopsis>Father homesteaded in 1884; came to America at age 19
               from Sweden. Talked Swedish in the home.
               
            </synopsis>
         </point>
         <point>
            <time>360</time>
            <title>1893 Depression; Coxey's Army got some boys from Troy to join</title>
            <synopsis>1893 Depression: hard to get money for postage.
               Coxey's Army got some Troy boys to join. "The last
               250 in the state of Idaho." Hoboes.
               
            </synopsis>
         </point>
         <point>
            <time>660</time>
            <title>Early Troy a thriving town; railroad traffic; shooting of Marshall Hayes by Paine
               sly; prospecting and mining
               
            </title>
            <synopsis>Early Troy a thriving little town. Railroad traffic,
               livery barns. Shooting of Marshall Hayes by Paine Sly,
               Prospecting and mining. The Copper Chief.
               
            </synopsis>
         </point>
         <point>
            <time>960</time>
            <title>Paul Smith in 1894 decides to leave, but convinced to stay by Dernam and Kaufman</title>
            <synopsis>Paul Smith in 1894 decides to leave, but is convinced
               to stay by Dernam and Kaufman. They talk quite a few
               people into staying, and help them do it.
               
            </synopsis>
         </point>
